cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the use of the categorical compositional distributional (DisCoCat) model of meaning, which is a model used in computational linguistics and natural language processing, falling under the category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of matrices and methods from the logical setting, which are relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence, falling under the categories of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates different methods in a disambiguation task, which involves analyzing and processing data, falling under the categories of "cs.CC" (Computational Complexity) and "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms).
